      Product Description

      UGREEN SATA to USB 3.0 Adapter Cable for 2.5/3.5 Inch Hard Drive Disk HDD and SSD, with Power Adapter

      UGREEN USB 3.0 to SATA III Adapter cable enables quick access to 2.5/3.5 inch SSD and HDD, and offers an easy way for booting up old hard disks, upgrading PC storage, cloning hard disks, recovering & retrieving data of decommissioned laptops, and expanding storage. You are free of opening a computer panel for troublesome installation. More effective and convenient.

      Faster Speed With UASP

      features latest SATA III 6Gbps internal and USB 3.0 5Gbps external and delivers blazing data transmission rate up to 5Gbps. Enhanced with accelerated transmission protocols-UASP (USB Attached SCSI Protocol) and TRIM, the SATA 3 USB Adapter enables you to take the full advantage of SSD drives and realize 70% faster than traditional HDD drives.

      Simple to Use

      * Plug & play, driver-free for all devices.

      * Support hot-swapping. No need to swith off your laptop while exchanging the connected hard disks.

      * Power supply required for 3.5 inch hard drive disk.

      Wide Compatibility

      * USB 3.0 Male Connection: Laptops running Windows 10/8.1/8/7/XP/Vista, Mac OS, Linux or Chrome OS; Game consoles like PS4, PS4 Pro, PS3, Xbox one, Xbox 360; Raspberry Pi; TV; Router, etc.

      * SATA 15+7 Pin Female Connection: 2.5" SATA III / II / I HDD and SSD, compatible with WD Blue PC Hard Drive, WD Black 3.5", WD Green SATA 3, Seagate Barracuda 3.5/2.5, Seagate IronWolf, Toshiba P300 3.5", Seagate FireCuda, Samsung 860 EVO / 850 EVO SATA III, Crucial BX500, Kingston SATA A400, PNY CS900, TCSUNBOW / Silicon Power / DREVO / YUCUN internal Solid State Drives,etc.

      Application Step

      * For using it:

      Plug the hard drive into the adapter Connect the adapter with power Connect it to your computer via the USB interface

      *For Removing it:

      Click the disk icon, choose Eject Hard Drive to remove the hardware safely Disconnect the 12V 2A power adapter Disconnect the usb port

      Important Note

      1. No extra power required for 2.5" HDD/SDD.

      2. For 3.5" HDD/SDD, Please connect the 12V/2A power adapter in the package for stable transmission.

      3. For UASP, only when your devices, hard drives and system are UASP supported, then the speed can be 20% faster.

      4. Do not support BLU-RAY DVD, CD-ROM, DVD-ROM, CD-RW, DVD+RW Combo devices.

      5. If your hard drive is new, please make a partition before using it. If your hard drive is old and it doesn't work, please back up the data first and then make a partition for a try.

          aTypicalEngineer808
          TOP 500 REVIEWERVINE VOICE
          5.0 out of 5 stars works as expected, might want to be careful in what order you plug in the AC adapter
          Reviewed in the United States on March 24, 2019
          Verified Purchase
          Good fit and finish. I tested this on several drives, both 2.5 and 3.5 inch. For the 3.5, I used the power adapter, and for the 2.5, I used it without the power adapter. One nice feature I like for this one is the blue power light, which illuminates when you have a drive plugged in and powered up (either plugged in with the AC adapter for 3.5, or plugged into the USB for 2.5).

          Notes: The item says "plug and play, hot-swapping"; however, (being an electrical engineer), I think the best way to connect and power up would be in this order: 1) plug the adapter into the drive, 2) connect the power (for a 3.5 drive), and 3) plug the USB in. Then to disconnect, perform in reverse order. While it might work in a different order, this would most closely resemble how a HDD (hard disk drive) would be powered up in normal operation. Specifically the step you might want to avoid is plugging the adapter to the HDD with the AC adapter plugged in.

          Recommendations: Manufacturer, provide specific connection steps for both scenarios (3.5 with AC adapter, 2.5 without).

          Jeremy Lee Potocki
          5.0 out of 5 stars Great adapter. Also good for Single Board Computers as well.
          Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2019
          Verified Purchase
          I tested this device with my PC, Laptop, Samsung 4K smart TV (2017 model,) Raspberry Pi, and Odroid C2 here are the results:
          Blu Ray Burner: Can play movies, and write data (though not at top speed due to USB 3.0 limitations.)
          3.5" HDD: Read & Write as well as name branded external HDDs.
          2.5" HDD: Same as above, but can work without Power Adapter (exceptions with some Single Board Computers.)
          2.5" Hybrid drives: also same as above, BUT I would highly recommend the use of the power supply without the power adapter it acted "funny."
          2.5" Runs well, but USB 3.0 has limits on speed. fastest speed I could achieve was 440MBps Read & 191MBps Write (on a Crucial 128GB SATA3 SSD normally get 550R & 420W on the PC). Also works without Power Adapter (exceptions with some Single Board Computers.)

          Works well with Smart TVs that have video playback features (SSDs & Hybrid Disk Drives can do 4K High Bit Rate Videos as long as your TV has proper codecs.) PCs, Laptops, and Single Board Computers work as well. If you only have have USB 2.0 ports on said devises you can only achieve the max 2.0 speeds (Blu Ray will not work well) to get best speed for 2.0 ports use SSD. You will need to use the Power Supply as well for best results with 2.0 ports.

          With that said Single Board Computers that use Micro USB to power the system (like Raspberry Pi) will need to use the Power Adapter as well or you may run into serious issues (especially if you're running a RetroPie setup) other than that it'll work just fine except Blu Ray (I thought it would be fun to try it out.)

          Overall this is a solid device that'll work well on multiple devises. I do hope they make a USB Type C version of this device that would allow all Devices to run at full SATA3 speeds.

          5.0 out of 5 stars Got it done
          Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2019
          Verified Purchase
          As other reviewers have said, I waited too long to invest into a product like this cable converter. Not being a techie, I did consult IT people years ago when my old PC died. I was told that it was possible to connect the "dead" hard drive to a new one so I could have salvaged many years' worth of personal (and therefore absolutely irreplaceable) files. At the time, I also consulted a data recovery company and was given an estimate running $1,000.

          I decided to simply keep the "dead" hard drive until the time came I'd attempt to salvage the data myself.           Lastly, make sure you "Eject Device" from within your OS (in the Windows 10 taskbar) BEFORE unplugging a disk. Some disks, specifically hard disks, need to "park" the drive head and other things when they power off, and you risk damaging the drive if you simply unplug a drive before "Ejecting" it via the OS.
